-- OCBC shares fall after bank announces rights issue 
-- By Anshuman Daga
-- Sun Aug 17, 2014 09:14PM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Aug 18 (Reuters) - Shares in Oversea-Chinese Banking Corp <OCBC.SI> declined as much as 1.4 percent in early trade after Singapore's second-biggest lender unveiled plans to raise S$3.37 billion ($2.7 billion) in a rights issue to strengthen its capital after the recent acquisition of Hong Kong's Wing Hang Bank Ltd <0302.HK>.

The shares were down in a broader market <.FTSTI> which fell 0.3 percent on Monday.